nd agencies would still need to be paid for, and they would still protect you whether you like it or not.<br /><br />The only thing that would shift is that you'd be complaining about company ABC instead of the government.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br /><br />Take up my slack to provide me with what?  And who's fault is that?  <br /><br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />I've already explained several things that are provided to you. You seem to think that if the government didn't do them, they would get done by an all powerful "free market".  <br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br /><br />The State is a thief, and you are both its willing victim and it's accomplice.  You are its stooge; I, on the other hand, am a real American trying to promote capitalism.<br /><br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Whatever I am, you sir are a criminal, and you're promoting criminal ideas.  If your ideas are so good, why haven't we switched over to them?  Aren't the peope who vote the same Americans that you don't think would ever fall for any type of scam, could never be swindled, and thus don't need any type of protection.  Why aren't politicians with your ideas in charge of the country?<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br /><br />What do you do for society?  Pay your taxes? So did Ted Bundy.<br /><br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Yes, I pay my taxes, I <b>contribute</b>.  You, on the other hand, don't do shit, you <b>leech</b>.  In the taxes department, Ted Bundy was indeed better than you are.  Just like Ted Bundy, even if you <i>did</i> pay your taxes, you would sti