t bad, but the way you present it is stupid.  Your views are so extreme that they no longer make any sense.  To argue that the privatization of some government agencies might lower the burden on the tax payer is a noble idea if one can find a way to do so without endagering the citizens.  To say the government is robbing the citizens blind for no reason is simply stupidity.  To claim that you don't get anything you want for your tax dollars is dumb.  Yes, you probably pay for some things that you'll never use, but lots of other people have paid for things that you <i>do</i> use.</span></font></td>
